# ===============================================
# GIT SETUP GUIDE
# ===============================================

To make this a proper Git-maintainable project:

1. INITIALIZE GIT REPOSITORY
   --------------------------------
   cd lora_visualizer
   git init

2. CREATE .gitignore
   --------------------------------
   # Copy the content above into a file named .gitignore
   # Place it in the root directory (lora_visualizer/)

3. STAGE ALL FILES
   --------------------------------
   git add .

4. FIRST COMMIT
   --------------------------------
   git commit -m "Initial commit: LoRA visualizer with all features"

5. CREATE GITHUB REPOSITORY (OPTIONAL)
   --------------------------------
   # Go to github.com and create a new repository
   # Then connect your local repo:
   
   git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/lora-visualizer.git
   git branch -M main
   git push -u origin main

6. RECOMMENDED BRANCH STRUCTURE
   --------------------------------
   main          # Stable release branch
   develop       # Development branch
   feature/*     # Feature branches

   # Create develop branch:
   git checkout -b develop

7. TYPICAL WORKFLOW
   --------------------------------
   # Create feature branch
   git checkout -b feature/new-visualization
   
   # Make changes and commit
   git add .
   git commit -m "Add new visualization feature"
   
   # Merge back to develop
   git checkout develop
   git merge feature/new-visualization
   
   # Delete feature branch
   git branch -d feature/new-visualization

8. USEFUL GIT COMMANDS
   --------------------------------
   git status                    # Check status
   git log --oneline            # View commit history
   git diff                     # See changes
   git checkout -- <file>       # Discard changes
   git reset --hard HEAD        # Reset to last commit
   git tag v1.0.0              # Create version tag
   git push --tags             # Push tags to remote

9. COMMIT MESSAGE CONVENTIONS
   --------------------------------
   feat: Add new feature
   fix: Bug fix
   docs: Documentation changes
   style: Code formatting
   refactor: Code refactoring
   test: Add tests
   chore: Maintenance tasks

   Example:
   git commit -m "feat: Add QLoRA visualization support"
   git commit -m "fix: Correct gradient flow animation"
   git commit -m "docs: Update README with installation steps"

10. RELEASE PROCESS
    --------------------------------
    # Tag releases with semantic versioning
    git tag -a v1.0.0 -m "Release version 1.0.0"
    git push origin v1.0.0
    
    # Create release notes
    # - List new features
    # - List bug fixes
    # - List breaking changes